    // if the exact answers were the same, then the model with more answers that were off by 1 was better,
    // if the exact answers and the answers that were off by 1 were the same, then the model with more answers that were off by 2 was better
    // and so on and so on
    {
      "modelName": "exampleModelOne",
      "answers": [
        17, // 17 exact answers, meaning if the original score was 5, the model's answer was also 5, if it was 4, the model's answer was also 4, and so on.
        7, // 7 answers that were off by 1, meaning if the original score was 5, the model's answer was either 4 or 6, if it was 4, the model's answer was either 3 or 5, and so on.
        3, // 3 answers that were off by 2, meaning if the original score was 5, the model's answer was either 3 or 7, if it was 4, the model's answer was either 2 or 6, and so on.
